msItem.title: Materia Medica
msItem.explicit: ... neach doghabh hé an Gaidheilcc. F.i.n.i.t. Amen. Misi Gilla Coluim.

note.p: The second word is simply ".m." in the MS, which has been expanded as "Muire" above. However, O'Connor (2018) has "mathgamna" based on other manuscripts.
There is a lenition mark over the "o" of "ol".
A suspension stoke originally appeared over the tironian et (= "eter"?) but an attempt has been made to erase it.
The word is repeated in the MS.
Other MSS (O'Connor 2018: 85) add "& epaticum" at this point, which the sentence does indeed seem to require.
Other manuscripts stipulate that the herb should not be gathered during this period.
There is an "a" written below the "i" of "inat", but there is nowhere for it to be cogently inserted.
